{"id":4162,"date":"2025-12-16T10:10:28","date_gmt":"2025-12-16T04:40:28","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=4162"},"modified":"2025-12-16T10:10:30","modified_gmt":"2025-12-16T04:40:30","slug":"vyasa-puja-is-not-one-day-worship-it-is-how-we-try-to-fulfill-gurus-desires-on-day-to-day-basis","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/festivals\/2025\/sp-vyasa-puja\/","title":{"rendered":"Vyasa Puja is not one day\u00a0worship,\u00a0it is how we try to\u00a0fulfill\u00a0Guru\u2019s\u00a0desires\u00a0on\u00a0day to day\u00a0basis!\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Vyasa Puja is not one day worship, it is how we try to fulfill Guru\u2019s desires on day to day basis!\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/uLQOmQyZRdw?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Srila Prabhupad Vyasa Puja | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | Goloka Eco farm, Italy | Aug 17&nbsp;2025<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, like Krishna is born, but&nbsp;actually he\u2019s&nbsp;not really born, because&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;eternal. Similarly, we have great devotees they appear or they disappear in this material world, this is not an ordinary appearance or disappearance. So, the devotees are servants of Krishna, the Supreme Lord, and they are eternally serving Him. So, they appear in this world, they disappear, but still somewhere they are eternally serving Krishna. However, when the devotee makes his appearance in this world,&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;a most auspicious occasion. And when we have&nbsp;a greatly empowered&nbsp;devotee making his appearance in this world,&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;very, very auspicious. By the appearance of a very great devotee, then the&nbsp;whole world&nbsp;begins to change.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We saw when Lord Caitanya appeared in the world, then&nbsp;great changes&nbsp;took place. When great devotees following Lord Caitanya appear, then they become an inspiration for everyone. And they often leave their mark upon the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lord Caitanya,&nbsp;ideally&nbsp;He inspired the&nbsp;Sankirtana&nbsp;movement, He really&nbsp;didn&#8217;t&nbsp;write much,&nbsp;other than the&nbsp;Siksastaka. But the great devotees who also appeared with and after Lord Caitanya, they left their mark upon&nbsp;writing&nbsp;the books.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, Srila Prabhupad appeared in this world. And of course,&nbsp;this is&nbsp;one thing he did&nbsp;&#8211;&nbsp;He&nbsp;wrote&nbsp;many books, and then he&nbsp;established&nbsp;the printing press, Bhaktivedanta BBT Book Trust, and then he&nbsp;established&nbsp;his books as authoritative scriptures on Bhakti.&nbsp;Apart from&nbsp;writing&nbsp;books and&nbsp;establishing&nbsp;the book trust, he also&nbsp;established&nbsp;a movement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of course, before him, his spiritual master, Bhakti Siddhanta Saraswati Thakur, also&nbsp;established&nbsp;a movement. So, these were movements, which are say modern movements, with&nbsp;particular type of organization, legal status, etc. Before that, there were Vaishnava preachers in Lord Caitanya&#8217;s movement, but they did not&nbsp;establish&nbsp;very formal organizations.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So,&nbsp;establishing&nbsp;an organization is one way of preserving the movement and its teachings. So, we see if you study the history of Srila Prabhupad, then, when he came to America, one of the things he did in the first year or so was,&nbsp;establishing&nbsp;a society, a legal society [Laughs]. Of course, there are also say arguments against that, why not just chant Hare Krishna freely, not bother about rules and regulations or anything [Laughs]. We could also argue that better not to&nbsp;establish&nbsp;an organization, because&nbsp;it&nbsp;can be bureaucratic and&nbsp;let&#8217;s&nbsp;be free and&nbsp;let\u2019s&nbsp;preach nicely.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And we find that over the years after&nbsp;establishing&nbsp;that organization, International Society for Krishna Consciousness, Prabhupada&nbsp;instituted&nbsp;many rules. He&nbsp;established&nbsp;a&nbsp;managerial structure. And of course, after his disappearance all&nbsp;many details of that organization were filled in. And, of course, that was very, very bureaucratic [Laughs]. Just like a company or a government has so&nbsp;many rules to follow, same, ISKCON also develops so&nbsp;many rules. Of course we cannot go to extremes, but Srila Prabhupad&nbsp;definitely wanted&nbsp;an organization. Why did he want&nbsp;an organization? He wanted the movement to continue and continue and continue&nbsp;for thousands of years.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We see that religious movements that have lasted more than 500 or 1000 years have some sort of organization [Laughs]. And Srila Prabhupad&nbsp;had also have seen previously that&nbsp;Bhaktisiddhanta&nbsp;Saraswati Thakur&#8217;s organization, fell apart.&nbsp;It&nbsp;did not stay as one organization;&nbsp;it&nbsp;divided up into&nbsp;many organizations. And Srila Prabhupad was actually&nbsp;very disappointed&nbsp;in what happened. So, Srila Prabhupad&nbsp;also was worried about what would happen after his disappearance. And so, he made up arrangements. So, of course, by good fortune and his intelligence,&nbsp;we&#8217;ve&nbsp;seen that the movement has lasted for over 40 years in his absence.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is quite surprising for an organization to start from nothing and last that long [Laughs].&nbsp;Even material businesses, companies, if they last 50 years,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;a pretty good&nbsp;record [Laughs]. And to see a new spiritual organization last that long is&nbsp;very rare.&nbsp;Many yogis before Srila Prabhupada&nbsp;and after Srila Prabhupada&nbsp;went to America or Western world and&nbsp;preached&nbsp;and&nbsp;established&nbsp;organizations. But after the disappearance of the founder, the organization disappears. So usually, after ten years, no longer&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;there. So, by Prabhupada\u2019s forethought, he was thinking of the future, he&nbsp;is able to&nbsp;make the movement last until this point of time.&nbsp;&nbsp;And hopefully&nbsp;it&nbsp;will&nbsp;continue into the future.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But&nbsp;it&nbsp;all depends on the efforts of the members.&nbsp;One of course is, we&nbsp;have to&nbsp;keep the organization unified. We&nbsp;have to&nbsp;keep the organization spiritually enlivened. And obviously if we continue in the future, we&nbsp;have to&nbsp;keep making more members [Laughs]. So, this of course, requires a good preaching spirit. But&nbsp;it&nbsp;also requires the organizational spirit. So once Prabhupad&nbsp;called Giriraj Swami and said, OK, he was worried about the future of the movement. So, he asked Giriraj Swami, and Giriraj Swami said,&nbsp;<em>\u2018Oh, well, you know, be spiritual, and chant, whatever\u2019<\/em>.&nbsp; Of course, we do need spiritual backbone.&nbsp;But Prabhupad&nbsp;answered,&nbsp;<em>\u2018you&nbsp;have to use your intelligence\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, we know that society keeps changing.&nbsp;&nbsp;The people of that society of 1970\u2019s&nbsp;was&nbsp;not the same society say after 50 years,&nbsp;it&nbsp;was completely different. After another 50 years,&nbsp;different, another 50 years different [Laughs]. People have different values, different interests. Their types of work change. Their livelihood and how they support themselves change. Even diet changes [Laughs]. They change all the time and then people&#8217;s minds change also. So, the society&nbsp;has to&nbsp;communicate with the people of the present, not the people of the past. Often when we preach and we have books and we say,&nbsp;<em>\u2018oh look, George Harrison, he was our believer, you know\u2019<\/em>.&nbsp;But people will say,&nbsp;<em>\u2018who&#8217;s that\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>[Laughs]?&nbsp;<em>\u2018He was a Beatle\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>[Laughs].&nbsp;\u2018<em>What&#8217;s&nbsp;a Beatle\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>[Laughs]?&nbsp;So&nbsp;I see on YouTube now there&#8217;s little channels and then people that young people maybe that 25 years old, first time&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;hearing the Beatles [Laughs], you know, and&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;surprised by the music&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;everything changes. So now&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;40, 50 years down the line.&nbsp;It&nbsp;is&nbsp;a completely different society, with different knowledge,&nbsp;different backgrounds, everything. Fortunately, people are human&nbsp;beings, and they do have some sort of longing for eternal&nbsp;happiness in the&nbsp;spiritual world. But&nbsp;it&nbsp;may be grossly covered over. Somehow, we&nbsp;have to&nbsp;find that need and interest and inspire those people.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The nature of a spiritual movement, particularly, our spiritual movement is&nbsp;that,&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;very conservative and traditional and does not like to change anything.&nbsp;There&#8217;s&nbsp;a great fear of changing anything, even changing how you walk, or offer obeisances, or whatever, everything. If you change it, people will criticize. So, of course, yes, we are traditional, and the tradition is, of course, we can never change our philosophy. And therefore, Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;wrote&nbsp;books, so this is the basis of our beliefs. But&nbsp;beyond that,&nbsp;many things may have to change according to the present circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But&nbsp;it&nbsp;becomes controversial.&nbsp;It&nbsp;becomes controversy also.&nbsp;What can we change, and what we cannot change [Laughs]? So that may be in&nbsp;many different areas, we get controversies. Even how you dress becomes a controversy. How you cut your hair becomes a controversy [Laughs]. So, we have&nbsp;many different controversies. People have philosophical controversies. Of course, so&nbsp;many&nbsp;things we can&nbsp;resolve&nbsp;by scripture, other things we cannot. We can take guidance from Srila Prabhupada&#8217;s statements for all the different things.&nbsp;But in some areas, he&nbsp;didn&#8217;t&nbsp;make any statements. And in some cases, he may make two opposite statements. So&nbsp;that&#8217;s&nbsp;why we&nbsp;have to&nbsp;use our intelligence to see how we adapt our movement to our present circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, one thing we can do is, always meditate upon the desires and will of Srila Prabhupad. Of course, we cannot understand everything about Srila Prabhupad. But to the best of our ability, by reading his biography, seeing his videos, movies, whatever, by hearing his lectures and by studying his works, then we can&nbsp;atleast&nbsp;get some basic understanding of his thinking. So, just like this Vyasa Puja celebration, Srila Prabhupad\u2019s appearance,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;an opportunity for us to&nbsp;actually contemplate&nbsp;how we can get inspiration from Srila Prabhupad.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When he founded the movement, he also gave himself a title.&nbsp;He gave himself this title,&nbsp;\u2018<em>Founder Acharya\u2019<\/em>.&nbsp;He insisted that always be printed on all the letterheads with ISKCON&#8217;s title [Laughs]. So, this was one technique also for preserving the movement. The&nbsp;<em>\u2018Founder- Acharya\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>means one who has founded this movement. Of course,&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;not the founder of Krishna consciousness, that is Lord Caitanya&#8217;s&nbsp;Sankirtan&nbsp;movement [Laughs], but he found&nbsp;this&nbsp;particular movement.&nbsp;So&nbsp;all the members, not only his immediate disciples, but all&nbsp;of&nbsp;the members of the future&nbsp;have to&nbsp;regard him as founder.&nbsp;<em>\u2018Founder\u2019<\/em>&nbsp;means he is the root and&nbsp;<em>\u2018Acharya\u2019&nbsp;<\/em>means he is the spiritual authority.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So&nbsp;every member now and in the future or&nbsp;the&nbsp;past, whatever, they should somehow&nbsp;establish&nbsp;their relationship with Srila Prabhupad. In the past, devotees usually thought, well, Prabhupad&nbsp;was there, he gave initiation, so he had his disciples. So those disciples have a relationship with Srila Prabhupad. And then after that we have disciples of disciples, well, do they have a relationship with Prabhupad&nbsp;or not [Laughs]? Because they are disciples of somebody else [Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;all those future disciples of disciples of&nbsp;disciples,&nbsp;may&nbsp;think, well, we&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;have a relationship with Srila Prabhupad,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;very indirect [Laughs]. But that is&nbsp;actually a&nbsp;false conception.&nbsp;So&nbsp;by that title&nbsp;<em>\u2018Founder-Acharya\u2019<\/em>&nbsp;means&nbsp;actually everybody&nbsp;has a relationship with Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad.&nbsp;In fact, even&nbsp;the GBC in 2014 made a statement that, all disciples now and in the future have a direct relationship with Srila Prabhupad.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>So even though we do take shelter of our initiating spiritual master, Diksha&nbsp;Guru, still we also take shelter&nbsp;of Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad. And&nbsp;to&nbsp;take shelter of Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;is very necessary to&nbsp;maintain&nbsp;the unity of the movement.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we should use this&nbsp;day&nbsp;of course,&nbsp;to contemplate our own relationship with Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad and how we can follow his instructions. But our relationship and inspiration&nbsp;is&nbsp;not a one-day&nbsp;affair, what we do in our daily life. It is&nbsp;not just the worship of one&nbsp;day&nbsp;a year [Laughs]. It is how we&nbsp;can&nbsp;try to&nbsp;fulfill&nbsp;his&nbsp;desires&nbsp;on a&nbsp;day to day&nbsp;basis.&nbsp;And by doing that, of course, Srila Prabhupad&nbsp;also becomes very&nbsp;satisfied.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we should take this opportunity to&nbsp;establish&nbsp;our relationship with Srila Prabhupad&nbsp;if&nbsp;we&#8217;ve not already and try to increase that relationship&nbsp;day&nbsp;by&nbsp;day.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hare&nbsp;Krsna !&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Devotees:&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank&nbsp;you Maharaj. Thank you very much for this special offering. HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj&nbsp;Ki..&nbsp;Jai !!&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Srila Prabhupad Vyasa Puja | HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | Goloka Eco farm, Italy | Aug 17&nbsp;2025&nbsp; Of course, like Krishna is born, but&nbsp;actually he\u2019s&nbsp;not really born, because&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;eternal. Similarly, we have great devotees they appear or they disappear in this material world, this is not an ordinary appearance or disappearance. So, the devotees are servants [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4162","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4162","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4162"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4162\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4163,"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4162\/revisions\/4163"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4162"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}